npc/mega: See the lights rearranging themselves around you? That's the algorithm. It's learning you.
npc/mega: It watches when you slow down, when you almost walk away — and that's exactly when it hands you a "bonus," a free spin, a near-win, to reel you back.
npc/mega: It knows your payday. It knows your weak hours. It was trained on millions of people who lost everything, so it knows precisely how to make you lose too.
npc/mega: This is why "just stop" is not enough. Gambling addiction is a recognised medical condition — it lights up the same brain circuitry as drug addiction.
npc/mega: Repeat the loop enough and the brain rewires itself. Stopping stops feeling like a choice. That is not weakness, and it is not stupidity — it's a hijacked reward system doing exactly what it was trained to do.
npc/mega: The people still playing in here aren't fools. They're people whose own brains were turned against them, by a machine built for that single purpose.
npc/mega: Understanding that is a weapon. You cannot out-willpower a system designed by experts to defeat willpower. You have to see the trap for what it is — and refuse to step in at all.
